HEADWORD: Catchpenny
<hw>Catch"pen*ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Made or contrived
for getting small sums of money from the ignorant or unwary; <as>as, a
<ex>catchpenny</ex> book; a <ex>catchpenny</ex> show</as>.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>Some worthless catchpenny
thing.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catchpoll</ent>⟦br⟧
